<bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
<head>Biographical/Historical Information 
</head>
<p>The Quarles family have been prominent members of Albemarle County and surrounding counties since the 1700s. A branch of Priddy's Creek is named Quarles Creek. Family members of owned hundreds of acres at Priddy's Creek, Rock Hall, Mechunk, and Buck Island. Modern prominent family members include Dr. Lawrence R. Quarles who was the Dean of Engineering at the University of Virginia.
</p>
</bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
<head>Scope and Content
</head>
<p>F1: Certificates
Various school certificates from the early 1900s (4)</p>
<p>F2: Professional Activities of Dr. Lawrence R. Quarles
Business Card, Radio Program, Name Tag, Jury Summons, UVA Pamphlet for the School of Engineering</p>
<p>F3: Greeting Cards
At least one to Dean Quarles</p>
<p>F4: Photographs
Lawrence R. Quarles
Misc. photos from the 1920s and 60s.</p>
<p>F5: Ephemera
Sheet Music dedicated to Rev E.W.D. Isaac Sr., D.D.</p>
</scopecontent>

